HEADWORD: Foulder
<hw>Foul"der</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>fouldre</ets> lightning, fr. F. <ets>foudre</ets>, OF. also
<ets>fouldre</ets>, fr. L. <ets>fulgur</ets>. See
<er>Fulgor</er>.]</ety> <def>To flash, as lightning; to lighten; to
gleam; to thunder.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> ⟦ldquo⟧Flames of
<xex>fouldering</xex> heat.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Spenser.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
